description: Meet Rune, Rath and Thats--three warriors with dragon blood running through their veins. They've sworn allegiance to the Dragon Lord Lykouleon, and whenever evil shows up in the kingdom, it's up to the three Dragon Knights to save the day. The mighty trio are on their way home for rest and feasting when an incompetent witch and a demon rudely interrupt them. It's no fun fighting bad guys on an empty stomach! Oh well, it's all in a day's work when you're the most famous warriors in the land...
name: Vol. 1

description: An origin story! This 2nd installment in the series takes us back to 'before they were Dragon Knights.' In the fabulous kingdom of Draqueen, Lykouleon and his court are always vigilant against the forces of the Yokai demons, but they have no army to fight back. When a stubborn thief and a love-struck elf cross his path, he may have found just the ones to help him. Ahh, from such humble beginnings...
name: Vol. 2

description: Beneath Draqueen Castle lies a secret staircase to a forbidden room, and behind a hidden door lies ... well, no one knows, but it's probably pretty scary. The Dragon Knights are finally back home and at peace, but all is not well with the Kingdom now that Nadil is dead. His agents are on the rise, amassing an army to try to steal back Nadil's head. Meanwhile, a young demon is found inside the castle. Could he be a spy? Or is there really dissension in the demon ranks?
name: Vol. 3

description: With the Yokai forces amassing to attack the castle, an air of tension has fallen over the court and Rath is itching for Bierrez to show his face again, Thatz salivates for treasure and food, and Rune loses himself in a world of self-contemplation, trying to regain the elfin healing powers he lost upon joining the Dragon Tribe. But no matter how disparate their concerns, they must band together with the Dragon Lord Lykouleon and the other Dragon Officers to face Nadil's army. However, Zoma goes missing, Rath may be dying, and the heroes are beginning to show signs of doubt about their chances against a formidable foe.
name: Vol. 4

description: The Dragon Knights have been dispatched again in the service of the Dragon Lord, but this time to three different corners of the realm. Thatz, reluctantly reunited with Kitchel, journeys to find the three treasures. Rath, reluctantly guarding Cesia, travels to Mt. Mfartha. And Rune, having regained his elfin powers, heads toward the Faerie Forest, concerned for his brethren. The battle to save the peaceful lands is looking grim, and with Kharl the Alchemist vying for the power of both Cesia and Nadil, the Dragon Tribe is taking a risk by spreading its forces so thin, especially with reports of demon forces closing in on them from all sides.
name: Vol. 5

description: Lord Lykouleon has dispatched the three Dragon Knights to separate corners of the realm. Rune journeys to the Faerie Forest to investigate reports of its demise at the hands of the demons. On his way, he partners up with a mysterious drifter and a little girl being hunted by the Yokai. However, things are not as they appear, for the little girl possesses a power beyond imagination, and good spirits turn bad as the forces of darkness continue their quest to take over the Forest. Only Rune and the mysterious drifter can save the Faeries from extermination!
name: Vol. 6

description: Kitchel and Ringsley are able to find the three treasures in the submerged water corridor in the lost continent of Arinas and encounter a corps of Dragon Warriors who are also trapped. But they cannot reach each other because of a spell that Kharl, the alchemist, has placed on them. Meanwhile Rath and Cesia close in on Mt. Mfartha. They stay at an inn where, as luck will have it, they meet up with Kai-stern. The owner of the inn asks Rath to defeat a nearby mischievous demon, a request he cannot turn down, leaving Kai-stern to journey up to Mt. Mfartha alone, a move that proves almost fatal as he encounters a strange creature - a deranged demon named Gil...
name: Vol. 8

description: With Thatz awaiting Kitchel and Ringleys as the two search an underwater cavern for the three treasures, and Rune embroiled in a bitter battle to save the Faerie Forest, Rath and Cesia are in the midst of Mt. Mfartha on a quest to resurrect the Dragon Dog Crewger. However, on their journey, their loyalties will be tested and their bond will be strained as each's connection to the demon world pulls them closer toward madness and betrayal. It will take their inner strengths to pull free from its grip, but will that be too late.
name: Vol. 7

description: In a deep--and perhaps long overdue--conversation, Kai-stern reveals to Cesia that he is searching feverishly for the Wind Dragon, the Dragon with the power to restore life. He wants to save the dying Rath. Cesia, is in search of the Wind Dragon to revive Crewger. Each agrees to keep this information from Rath, whom they fear might be consumed with senseless anger, as is his wont. Their fears are well founded when they meet up with Shydeman and Shyrendora, and their battle with the demon agents drives Rath into a vicious frenzy, hacking away with madness at the increasingly defenseless Gil, despite the best efforts of the Fire Dragon to quell his master's temper. It is here that Rath unveils the secret he has been keeping for years.
name: Vol. 9

description: Rath's mental state has deteriorated to the point that he lashes out at his closest allies who are duly concerned for his well-being. It is only after Cesia is apprehended that Rath comes to realize that his allies are all he has left and in his haste to rescue her, Rath is duped by her doppelganger and the demon within him is revived.
name: Vol. 10

description: Rath returns to the Dragon Castle consumed with exhaustion. Large numbers of demon forces close in on the castle. But Rath doesn't stay somnolent for long, and his awakening will mean death within the walls of the Dragon Castle, and the loss of a precious item within its vaults.
name: Vol. 11

description: Shydeman and Shyrendora, aided by a secret filial link to someone in the Dragon Castle, are able to weaken Lord Lykouleon's protective shield beyond the breaking point and attack the castle. As the demons attack, Rath begins the process of reviving Nadil, which involves cutting off his own head and placing the head of the fallen demon leader on his body. Cesia, Kai-stern and the rest of the Dragon court work to bring Rath back, but only a sacrifice from within their ranks will revive the fallen Dragon Knight...
name: Vol. 12

description: Nohiro, accompanied by three small Faeries (Shian, Hanakusuku and Miyabi), follows a call to the Eastern continent of Arinas, where he discovers Kharl's castle. There he finds an anxious and homicidal Garfakcy, uncovers a plot by Kharl to revive his master, and locates an imprisoned Tintlet. As the faerie-obsessed human attempts to save the day, Kitchel and Ringsley continue to search Arinas for the three treasures and a way out of the water cave in which they are trapped. Meanwhile, back in Draqueen, Rath awakens to the news that Cesia agreed to go with Nadil in exchange for the safety of the castle and vows to get her back.
name: Vol. 13

description: Having escaped from the water cave, Kitchel finds herself in disturbing and unfamiliar surroundings: the forest of the damned of Kainaldia. Meanwhile, Rath, Rune and Thatz summon a demon with Nadil's powers to help them find the kingdom of Kainaldia. Zoma also heads for the kingdom, hoping to take the Wind Staff to Cesi. As all roads lead to Kainaldia, an epic battle of strength is sure to ensue.
name: Vol. 14

description:
The Flintstones - Fred Who? - 9 pages

Hanna Barbera All Stars - 4 pages

The Flintstones - Shoe Enough - 6 pages

The Flintstones - Rub-A-Dub-Dub - 1 page

The Flintstones - Cool Man! - 1 page

The Flintstones - Mall Of The Wild - 6 pages

The Flintstones - Cry Baby - 1 page
name: Fred Who?

description: Rath, Rune and Thatz have double vision when they encounter two Tintlets: one, it is discovered, is a puppet Faerie, controlled by the demon Lim Kaana; the other is an empty shell. Even more distressing, their only chance of making Tintlet whole again is to brave the treacherous path through the dark kingdom of Kainaldia!
name: Vol. 15

description: Rune discovers Zoma and Kitchel bringing together the spirit and body of Tintlet. But the demon Lim Kaana stumbles upon the happenings, too, and in his anger attacks the group! Zoma is separated from them...but runs into Rath and Thatz, which may turn out to be a mixed blessing.
name: Vol. 16

description: To the surprise and amazement of Rath, Thatz and Zoma, a presumed-dead Fiji is now fully grown! The discovery is hopeful for the encouraged group, who stumbles upon Nadil's castle. With Fiji's skill and guidance, they cross the desert of the dead that surrounds the castle. Will all these good omens keep the gang out of harm’s way?
name: Vol. 17

description: As the enemy body count rises, Saabel finally realizes just how powerful Nadil has become. However, that's the least of Saabel's worries--Tetheus, a member of the dragon family, at long last emerges, and the two engage in a relentless bloody battle. Meanwhile, Rath, Rune, Tintlet and the others sneak into Nadil's castle...but what they find just might exterminate them for good!
name: Vol. 18

description: Kitchel, Tintlet and Lim are trying to find their way in Nadil's castle while the Dragon Knights are going head-to-head with Nadil. In a twisted turn of events, Rath's secret may lead to his own destruction! What choice will the Dragon Knights make?
name: Vol. 19

description: With all three Dragon Knights imprisoned, the fate of the Dragon Realm is in an unlikely set of hands...Zoma's! The dimunitive demon with a heart of gold has journeyed from Draqueen to Kainaldia to give the wind staff to Cesia. At last, he succeeds...or does he? With Cesia's evil alter ego in control, handing her the wind staff will give Nadil an unstoppable weapon. Will Zoma recognize Dark Cesia in time? Will the Dragon Knights find a way to escape from Nadil's dungeon? And what will happen to Kitchel and Ringleys now that they're on their own? The thrilling saga of Dragon Knights continues!
name: Vol. 20

description:
1. Bats in My Belfry (hosted by The Crypt Keeper / written by Al Feldstein : reprinted from: Tales From the Crypt (EC, 1950) #24) 
 
2. The Living Death! (hosted by The Old Witch / written by Al Feldstein : reprinted from: Tales From the Crypt (EC, 1950) #24)     
 
3. Midnight Snack! (hosted by The Vault Keeper / written by Al Feldstein : reprinted from: Tales From the Crypt (EC, 1950) #24)  
 
4. Scared to Death! (hosted by The Crypt Keeper / written by Al Feldstein, art by Wally Wood : reprinted from: Tales From the Crypt (EC, 1950) #24)
name: Bats in My Belfry

description:
Quick Draw McGraw - The Great Train Hold-Up! - 8 pages

Frog Talk - (Let's Race) - 1 page (untitled)

Quick Draw McGraw - Banana Guns - 1 page

Quick Draw McGraw - Gun Pox - 2 pages

Antone The Anteater - 1 page (Nose gets stung by bee and grows so he become Jewish)

Quick Draw McGraw - Blotch Cazzidy and the Sunbeam Kid - 3 pages

Quick Draw McGraw - Sneaker - 1 page

Quick Draw McGraw - Quiet, Please! - 3 pages

The Diaper Pin Kid - Befriending The Buffalo - 1 page poetry - by R.J. Simpson

Quick Draw McGraw - Make-Up - 1 page

Fat Dan and Bobbin - (Be Happy) - 1 page (untitled)

The Byrds by Phil Mendez - (Boiled Worms) - 1 page (untitled)

Quick Draw McGraw - Indians! - 1 page
name: The Great Train Hold-Up!

description: Presenting the sixth volume of IDW Publishing's deluxe hardcover collection of Chester Gould's timeless comic strip, Dick Tracy! Volume Six contains over 500 comic strips from the series' early years, this time covering material that originally ran from July 1939 through January 1941. This volume includes an introduction by Max Allan Collins and other historical material.

volume.name: The Complete Chester Gould's Dick Tracy

description: After months spent apart, Rath and Cesia have at last been reunited. Since her abduction at the hands of Nadil, Rath has faced all manner of demons, from weakest warrior demon to the mighty Demon Lord himself, all to save the half-demon fortuneteller who, whether he likes it or not, has captured the Dragon Knight's heart. But just because they've been reunited, doesn't mean that they're safe. Rath has been weakened by Nadil's attack and may have to make the ultimate sacrifice if the Dragon Realm is to find victory against the demon horde!
name: Vol. 21

description: Cesia vows to find Rath's spirit a corporeal body, and transports her and the Knights to the western continent of Dusis. In confusion, Gil travels to Dragon Castle to find out once and for all if his memories are false or real. A mysterious "acquaintance" appears before Bierrez and Gil. Who is this important "acquaintance?" Now, their mission and their lives are in jeopardy!
name: Vol. 22

description: The action picks up as Gil and his band of warriors move through the dragon castle, where they are searching for a mysterious treasure. Meanwhile, Kahaku (the water dragon) needs Saabel for some unspoken task--that may snare the infamous Dragon Emperor!
name: Vol. 23

description: Tetheus, Rune and Thatz encounter Shydeman and Fedelta in the Dragon Castle's sanctuary, where the Shydeman awakens the mourning monster Yusurugi. Our heroes must band together and combine the powers of the Blizzard Sword and the Furious Fire Sword if they are to have any chance of defeating Yusurugi! But will they have enough power to stop Shydeman and Fedelta first?
name: Vol. 24

description: "Someday, I will ask you to take over in my place." So was the promise made with Zoma that day at Dragon Castle. Using Zoma's body, which had become a bird, as a vessel, Rath finally awakens! Yusurugi is already spreading his wretched smoke across the plains, meaning that the end of the world is near. The final battle between Rath and Nadil has begun...
name: Vol. 25

description: It has all led to this... Lines have been drawn, sacrifices have been made, sides have been chosen...and now it all must end. Can our heroes defeat the forces of evil? Or will the dark wind that is Shydeman extinguish the flame of light forever? Find out as the epic saga of Dragon Knights comes to a thrilling close!
name: Vol. 26

description: The classic Chinese tale of The Three Kingdoms--with all your favorite historical figures cast as cute girls! As the Han Dynasty collapses, two mighty warriors--Zhang Fei and Guan Yu--stand strong against the tide of rebellion. But because these fighters are female, their dreams of fighting in the Imperial army are nothing but dreams...until they find a patron and like-minded brother in Liu Bei, an idealistic descedent of royalty with dreams of his own. Forging a pact, the three form a volunteer army dedicated to restoring peace, which means first defeating three deceptively adorable sisters who oppose them, and who have their own, definitely cuter, plan for China's future... One thing's for sure--history’s about to get a makeover!
name: Vol. 1

description: The classic Chinese tale of the Three Kingdoms with more curves than you can shake a stick at!  Dong Zhou is plotting her rise to power and first up is the purchase of some sexy swordswomen, our heroines Zhang Fei and Guan Yu. And though their brother of the sword, Liu Bei, bravely wins them back with the help of bouncy and belligerent Lu Bu, the war is far from over. The Essential Arts of Peace are still missing and Dong Zhou seems unstoppable in her quest to conquer the Chinese throne!
name: Vol. 2

description: Once again, we see Amina, the famous casualty from Matty's infiltration of the Trustwell cell back in DMZ Vol. 3. Since being rendered homeless and alone, she's been the very picture of tragic survival in the DMZ. In this third installment of 'Collective Punishment,' in the middle of the heavy bombing campaign, something quite unexpected enters her life.
name: Collective Punishment: Amina, Mother of One

description: Rin Amami is a good looking 15-year old kid with a lot of street smarts, but not much in the way of prospects. He's a street dancer, trying to make a buck. He has dreams of becoming a singer, of performing his own original music, but with a voice that sounds like a dying bullfrog, he has to settle for dancing to other people's tunes. That is, until a chance encounter with the newest boyband, THE BEATMEN, allows Rin to follow his dream of being a creator, rather than an imitator. After a series of odd circumstances put Rin onstage with the BEATMEN as a backup dancer, he finds himself actually singing with the band. Amazingly, his gruff voice seems to work. The crowd is stunned, the bandmembers are mixed and the band's manager is convinced that Rin possesses the legendary 'Dragon Voice,' which is fabled to be filled with "demonic charm and God-like brilliance." Unfortunately, the performance doesn't play so well on television and it looks like Rin's singing career may be over before it starts. However, Shino, the group's leader, sees something in Rin and convinces him to take another stab at it...
name: Vol. 1

description: No man, mouse or rat will be left behind as Joe embarks on a mission to save his fallen comrade Jack! But to do that, he'll have to enter the darkness of the Cellarworld and face off against the Black Horde - samurai rats that once served King Death itself in the penultimate chapter of the hit miniseries!
name: Chapter 7: Labyrinth of the Lost

description: Taking the timeless motif of 'young lovers on the run' to an alarming extreme, Erik and Ingrid, outcasts in 9th century Norway, strike a series of blows for individuality against the rigid conformity of the local priesthood in part 3 of 'Metal.'
name: Metal: Holy War

description: Special guest artist Ryan Kelly provides finishes over Peter Gross's art for "The Lives of Lizzie Hexam: A Choose-a-Story adventure." Enter the mind of Lizzie Hexam, Tom Taylor's fervent but enigmatic guardian, and explore the contradictory, impossible events that made her what she is. Is she a victim or champion? A madwoman or a saint? That's for you and fate to decide as you pick the story's path. The multiple Eisner-nominated series tells its most ambitious stand-alone story to date in an oversized, interactive issue!
name: The Many Lives of Lizzie Hexam

description: Typical. You ask a girl to marry you and she disappears to another planet. Still recovering from his brush with mental disintegration and his amputated thumb, John Constantine suspects that dark and powerful forces don't want him to be happy after he proposes to Epiphany...
name: Bloody Carnations, Part One: Oh Lucky Man

description: The battle of the boy bands hits a high note when The Beat Men invade the scene and start snatching up fans from Privee, the newest and hottest boy band! Privee strikes back, making it impossible for The Beat Men to book a gig. As a result, Beat Men take their concert to an outdoor venue. Will an act of God thrust them to stardom or rain on their show?
name: Vol. 2

description: Billy the Kid tries to take down a crooked government agent who has been stealing supplies from local Indian tribes.
name: The Apache's Gold!

description: Things have never been worse for the Beatmen. Red Shoes is bankrupt, their boss is in jail and now the band members have to work part-time jobs just to make ends meet. When they land roles as the Voice Rangers on a new TV series, will they be seen as the next big thing...or just a band of has-beens?
name: Vol. 3

description: The Voice Rangers are a big hit, bringing new life to the popular world of internet drama! But when they crash a live performance to gain publicity, will the final curtain go down on their budding careers, or will it set them sailing towards success? Being rock stars is hard work--dance lessons, vocal lessons, interviews, trying to get Red Shoes back on its feet...can the Beatmen handle it all?
name: Vol. 4

description: The Beatmen are sent back to school by their boss as part of their idol training. But even at a school for performers and superstars, you have to get good grades in math and literature! Unfortunately, after a disastrous performance on television, everyone thinks the Beatmen can't make the grade. As midterms approach quickly the Beatmen learn that studying music and studying math might just be mutually exclusive. Also when Shino's asthma suddenly kicks up, he may well decide to leave the group for good!
name: Vol. 5

description: The Beatmen's new CD is ready for release, but S-Field refuses to make the going easy for them, and releases the new Privee single on the same day. However, the number one American band on the charts turns out to be Baby Naked, fronted by a 16-year-old Japanese singer, Seiren! It doesn't take long before the three bands collide and have to compete for a major gig. But when Rin thinks his Dragon Voice might be holding back the Beatmen, he decides to put his money where his mouth is...
name: Vol. 6

description: The final trials to decide who will sing at Koshien begin--and the competition between the Beatment, Baby Naked and Privee is pretty intense! Just when Rin regains his courage, Toshi looks like he's going to lose his. The band that commands the attention of the fans will be crowned victor in this three-way musical duel! It's going to be a long, grueling, and brutal performance from all three bands.
name: Vol. 7

description: Could it be? Finally, the Beatmen win! Rin's Angel Form helps the Beatmen edge out Baby Naked and Privee to win the right to perform at the national baseball tournament in Koshien. Once there, the guys again choose to go against what was in the rehearsal--this time recruiting street dancers from Osaka to join their performance at the opening ceremony. But when someone from Rin's past catches his new tune, will the Beatmen's dreams be crushed?
name: Vol. 8

description: The Beatmen need lyrics to produce a full album, and Yuhgo can't come up with any. After hearing the undisputed underground champions of sound, Nobody Snafkin, the Beatman ask for a little writing assistance. Little do they know, that Nobody Snafkin want the wear the celebrity crown. Will the Beatman fade away in pop music history?
name: Vol. 9

description: The rivalry between the two bands, The Beatmen and Nobody Snafkin, heats up, and other larger, well-funded parties are getting involved. When rival car companies "corporate sponsor" each of the bands, only one thing can happen... That's right! A battle of the bands in front of a massive audience at the Twin Ring Motor Speedway! For the car companies it's a matter of business, for the bands it's a matter of honor... Will The Beatmen come out on top?
name: Vol. 10

description: Now a six-member team, the Mystery Society are off on several missions at once, including: retrieving Edgar Allan Poe’s stolen skull; fighting the government’s fear/smear campaign to undermine MS’s credibility; and staving off an all-out assault on their headquarters by arch nemesis, General Powell. With the help of Jules Verne, whose brain is now inside a robot, team leaders Nick Hammond and Anastasia Collins will be sure to live to see another day! We hope!

"Teenage Riot" finds the DV8 kids in full conflict with each other for the first time since crash-landing on this world. Bliss's tribe of female warriors is on the march, and she's set her sights on one of the other Deviants. In a blistering, lethal strike, she removes one of the players from the battlefield…but which one?
name: Teenage Riot

description: The ten-issue vampire epic on the bayou from the writer of the A Song of Ice and Fire novels continues in issue six! From the New York Times Best-selling author, George R. R. Martin, comes a tale of vampire clans, death and debauchery, legendary blood masters, and even a few epic steamboat races on the muddy Mississippi. This is Martin's FEVRE DREAM, an antebellum story of power, loss, and the fever of bloodlust. York and Marsh have finally, truly come to an understanding. What began as a business partnership shrouded in carefully constructed lies has now been flung into the burning light of the truth, the whole truth, and the two men now stand together as brothers-in-arms against a common enemy and towards a common goal -- the salvation of the human race. But are one man and one vampire strong enough to stand against the evil of Damon Julian? When the dark bloodmaster sets foot on the Fevre Dream, a bloody fight is about to begin... Each issue of this stunning full-color epic is illustrated by Rafa Lopez, an artist whose skilled line captures every moonlit drop of blood in delicious detail. Adapted by the Hugo-nominated author Daniel Abraham, this version of FEVRE DREAM stays faithful to Martin's original dark vision, while bringing the torture and joy of his vampires to almost-human life. This haunting series is available with Regular and Wraparound painted covers by Felipe Massafera and a very limited Nightmare retailer incentive.

volume.name: George R. R. Martin's Fevre Dream

description: It's the Glories' first day of school, and they've already landed themselves in detention! Now anywhere else that might just mean the start of a bad year, but they're about to find out when you're enrolled at Morning Glory Academy, corporal punishment takes on a whole new- and deadly - meaning! TAG: The most hotly anticipated new series of the summer continues! It's RUNAWAYS meets LOST from the writer of FORGETLESS and SHUDDERTOWN!

volume.name: Picture Stories from the Bible (New Testament)
